# TypeScript & React Style Rules

- Prefer explicit parameter types for callback args when TypeScript cannot infer them (e.g., sqlite callbacks `err: any`).
- Avoid calling functions in `useEffect` before their definitions; define functions first, then reference them in effects.
- Use early returns and avoid deep nesting.
- Keep API clients in `frontend/src/services` and avoid duplicating `axios` config.
- Do not import backend-only packages on the frontend (`jsonwebtoken`, `cookie-parser`, `resend`, `dotenv`, `express-rate-limit`).
- Use `useCallback` for stable function references passed to hooks/components.
- Keep environment/config access centralized in backend `config/*` files.

